@inflation , can you explain the details about the "soft-reset"?
I thought a process should be cleared by init even if its parent does not do that.
My problem seems to be something crashed in CUDA and result an "Unknown Error" which prevents the process to exit normally.

@inflation , doesn't work either(since the zombie processes still occupying the GPU card).
Some tensorflow users also encountered similar issues [here](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/1947). But no fix found yet.

I have given up and reboot the system already. Thanks for your help anyway.

@mli **Let me make the problem more clear**. I first trained ResNet-8 on Cifar10 dataset with **4 GPUs**, and achieved 0.838041 validation accuracy (ACC1) for the 40-th epoch. Then I resumed the checkpoint at 40-th epoch with **4 GPUs**, the evaluation accuracy becomes 0.847756 (ACC2). I also tried to resume the checkpoint at 40-th epoch with **single GPU**, the evaluation accuracy is also 0.847756 (ACC3).

Since ACC2 == ACC3 > ACC1, it is quite strange where the bug comes from. As ACC2 == ACC3, it indicates the multi gpu synchronization process is correct. But ACC2 > ACC1, it also indicates the multi gpu synchronization process might be wrong. This is quite confusing. 

@mli Your suggestion is equivalent to check for ACC2 and ACC3, and the results is correct for that. 

P.S. Note that I added an initial evaluation of the checkpointed model performance right after loading the parameters, which is before resuming training. https://github.com/taoari/mxnet/blob/finetune-api/python/mxnet/model.py#L230_L254 is simply a copy of the evaluation code of https://github.com/taoari/mxnet/blob/finetune-api/python/mxnet/model.py#L329_L350. ACC2 == ACC3 > ACC1 shows that https://github.com/taoari/mxnet/blob/finetune-api/python/mxnet/model.py#L230_L254 is OK for both single GPU and multi GPUs, but https://github.com/taoari/mxnet/blob/finetune-api/python/mxnet/model.py#L329_L350 is not correct for multi GPUs. However, these two parts are of exactly the same codes, it is quite confusing where the bug comes from.
